  "market_context": "Following a large-range day, NQ entered a consolidation day. The Asia session established a clear high and low range. London attempted to expand but failed to sustain displacement in either direction, creating conditions for a Seek and Destroy daily profile.",
  "key_observation": "Price repeatedly swept both the Asia high and Asia low without achieving sustained displacement or breakout in either direction. Each deviation outside the Asia range acted as a magnet, pulling price back inside, resulting in an indecision/doji-like daily candle.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identified that the prior day was a large-range day, flagging the current day as a probable consolidation/Seek and Destroy candidate.",
    "Step 2: Marked the Asia session high and low to define the reference range for the day.",
    "Step 3: Observed that when price deviated outside the Asia range, it acted as a magnet and price rebalanced back inside the range repeatedly during London.",
    "Step 4: Noted that London created most of the daily range through expansion moves, reducing the probability of a large New York directional move.",
    "Step 5: Watched price take out the Asia low — checked for displacement or breakout continuation; found none, price returned inside the range.",
    "Step 6: Watched price take out the Asia high — checked for displacement or breakout continuation on the upside; found none, price returned inside the range.",
    "Step 7: Extended the Asia range lines into the New York session and observed that New York also moved outside the range only to return back to equilibrium and the daily open, confirming the Seek and Destroy profile.",
    "Step 8: Marked premium and discount zones of the expanded range; noted price gravitated back to equilibrium of that range and the daily open, confirming no directional delivery."
  ],
  "outcome": "No trade taken. The analyst identified this as a low-probability environment and avoided directional trades. The daily candle closed as an indecision candle with minimal net movement.",
  "lessons": "When London creates most of the daily range, New York is unlikely to produce a large directional move. If price repeatedly sweeps both sides of the Asia range without displacement, it signals a Seek and Destroy day — avoid directional trades and wait for a higher-probability setup the following session.",
